{
  "texts": [
    "Instead of asking \"can I solve problem X effectively?",
    "\", we ask \"can I learn how to solve X effectively?\".",
    "If the answer is yes, the de facto run-time complexity might be trivially low given the appropriate training.",
    "Intuitively, if a specific problem has already been solved-e.g., having discovered the optimal action-combination for a certain situation (Sect. 4.1), an optimal reinforcement learning policy for an environment (Sect.",
    "4.3), or an action-rule in a strategic setting (Sect. 5)-the same solution may be applied in constant time O(1) to future cases given that the very same problem re-occurs."
  ]
}